It was a 3 person company, a music streaming service that streamed your music directly from your computer to anywhere, and also had a Pandora-like feature to create streams of music you didn't own but wanted to hear. I built the iOS and Android app, worked on the website, client and backend. Also did a whole bunch of other random stuff like making icons, building and maintaining the API, etc.

Before that, I was at Microsoft for 5 years. I spent 2 years on the Windows Core OS Division, and then 3 years on Windows Live Mesh.

I interned for a couple of semesters at National Instruments in Austin, Texas
